# SvelteKit / Svelte 5 Conventions

## Svelte 5 Reactivity

- Use runes (`$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`) — not the legacy `$:` reactive syntax.
- `$effect` must always return a cleanup function when it sets up subscriptions or timers:
  ```ts
  $effect(() => {
    const sub = store.subscribe(handler);
    return () => sub.unsubscribe();
  });
  ```
- Prefer `$derived` over `$effect` for computed values — effects are for side effects only.

## Data Loading

- Server data: use `+page.server.js` load functions for SSR seed data.
- Client data: write to Dexie (IndexedDB) in `+page.js` or components; use `liveQuery` for reactivity.
- Never fetch data directly in `$effect` on mount — use load functions or a dedicated store.
- All one-shot relay queries must have a timeout (default 5s).

## Component Structure

- One component per file. Keep components small and focused.
- Props via `let { prop } = $props()`.
- Avoid logic in templates — extract to `$derived` or helper functions.
- Use `{#if}`, `{#each}`, `{#await}` — not ternaries for complex branching.

## Routing

- `+page.svelte` — page UI
- `+page.server.js` — server-only load (SSR, DB queries)
- `+page.js` — universal load (runs on server and client)
- `+layout.svelte` — shared layout
- `+server.js` — API route (REST endpoint)

## TypeScript

- All files use TypeScript. No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow explicitly.
- Type route params and load data via generated `$types` from `.svelte-kit/types/`.
- Run `bun run check` to verify types — fix all errors before committing.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS utility classes. No custom CSS unless adding to `app.css` tokens.
- Follow the project's DESIGN_SYSTEM.md — use preset gradients, colors, and component patterns.
- Never invent new color values or gradients not in the design system.

## Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.svelte`. Routes: SvelteKit conventions (`+page.svelte`).
- Stores/utilities: `camelCase.ts`. CSS classes: Tailwind utilities only.

## Dependencies

- Run `bun install` after any `package.json` change.
- Prefer packages already in use over adding new ones.

## Build

- `bun run dev` — development server
- `bun run build` — production build
- `bun run check` — TypeScript + Svelte type check
